<BaseLayout
  title="Cancellation"
  description="Cancellation policy for Kamala Retreats."
>
  <article class="py-12 lg:py-20 mx-auto prose-kamala">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="font-light mt-4">Cancellation</h1>

    <p>All bookings are binding and non-refundable. Once paid, your room is held and the cost is committed.</p>

    <p>We say this kindly, but we say it firmly. We commit early — to venues, food, and practitioners — and we cannot recover those costs if a guest cancels. Travel insurance with retreat or cancellation cover is the simplest way to protect yourself if something gets in the way.</p>

    <p>If we have to cancel a retreat, you receive a full refund or, where possible, a transfer to a future weekend. The full picture — illness, transfers between guests, our cancellation, and what we do and don't cover — lives in the <a href="/legal/booking-terms">booking terms</a>. Please read those before you book.</p>

    <p>If circumstances have changed and you can no longer come, write to us at <a href="mailto:hello@kamalaretreats.com">hello@kamalaretreats.com</a>. We can't promise a refund, but we will treat you as a person, not a transaction.</p>

    <p class="text-xs">Last updated: 2026-05-09</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
